         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne botan. Garden, ¶ 9/10/70. ¶  ¶ It affords me very much pleasure, dear Mr Barlee, to introduce to you Mr Joachimi, ¶  a German gentleman, who held for about a dozen years a position in our pu...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.10.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Frederick Barlee</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Colonial Secretary's Office - letters received, acc. 36, vol. 657, ff. 65-6, State Records Office of Western Australia, Perth.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne botan. Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">9/10/70.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It affords me very much pleasure, dear Mr Barlee, to introduce to you Mr Joachimi,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Gustav Joachim?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> a German gentleman, who held for about a dozen years a position in our public works Office, he being a C.Es.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">check</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> and Architect. In the great reductions, which took place here lately in the public service Mr Joachimis appointment was also discontinued, and he is thus eager to obtain an other<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">sic - 2 words.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> scope for his talents, more particularly as he has a young family to support. Mr Joachimi <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is a man of remarkable ability and of excellent character and he would be a great acquisition to your colony even if he was only supported by the W. A. public in private practice.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>salutation your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The honorable Fr. Barlee <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Colonial Secretary of W. Australia/<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">.</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
